title: How will she find me?
text:
Wouldn't it be nice to wake up beside someone all rumpled from sleep, but naturally beautiful?



Wouldn't it be wonderful to go to our porch and watch our pets play from over a pair of steaming mugs?



Wouldn't we be so happy, 

living a simple life free of clutter and drama and pesticides and perfumes 

and other horrible things that don't exist in nature?



Wouldn't it be hilarious, playing strip scrabble in front of our fireplace?



Wouldn't we fit like a hand in a glove, 

you and me walking this green earth, 

kissing under the grey skies like we're twenty years younger?



Please find me

I can't wait to love your mind, soul, and skin.



this mortal coil doesn't last, 

I need you to stimulate my brain.

Cut through the day to day nonsense with your wit and warmth.

I'd do so for you
